From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 06:05:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] mmdevapi: Keep DualSense mono PnP AudioEndpoint skipped.

The controller speaker/effect endpoint is an app-facing MMDevice handle that
winepulse retargets to the currently connected Sony controller speaker sink.
It should not also be published as a normal fake PnP AudioEndpoint devnode.

The stale AudioEndpoint cleanup path accidentally re-enabled registration for
the newly created DualSense / DualSense Edge / DualShock mono endpoint after
removing stale controller speaker devnodes. Spider-Man Remastered can enumerate
that fake one-channel AudioEndpoint and hit its managed endpoint cast failure.

Keep deleting stale controller speaker AudioEndpoint devnodes, but leave
skip_audioendpoint set so the current controller mono endpoint remains MMDevice
only.
---
 dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c | 1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
--- a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
+++ b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
@@ -1080,7 +1080,6 @@ static void MMDevice_Register(const WCHAR *instguid, const WCHAR *friendly_name,
         if (skip_audioendpoint && is_dualsense_device_path(device_path))
         {
             remove_dualsense_audioendpoint_devices();
-            skip_audioendpoint = FALSE;
         }
 
         if (skip_audioendpoint)
